Eighty-thousand teachers across all primary schools in Kenya have been trained on how to use laptops in readiness for the Digital Literacy Programme.Deputy President William Ruto on Saturday said more than 96 per cent of public primary schools have been connected to electricity. This programme will revolutionise the process of learning in this country and put our children to be at par with their global counterparts," he said.Ruto spoke when he launched the Digital Literacy Programme at Burendwa Primary School in Kakamega county.